{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "Choose an installed toolchain to use as default.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/SwiftlyDocs\/documentation\/SwiftlyDocs"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/SwiftlyDocs\/documentation\/SwiftlyDocs\/use-toolchains"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Swiftly"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Use Swift toolchains"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swiftly toolchains include a variety of compilers, linkers, debuggers, documentation generators, and other useful tools for working with Swift. Using a toolchain activates it so that when you run toolchain commands they are run with that version.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When you install a toolchain you can start using it right away. If you don’t have any other toolchains installed then it becomes the default.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly install latest",
            "$ swift --version",
            "Swift version 6.0.3 (swift-6.0.3-RELEASE)",
            "Target: aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu",
            "$ swift build    # Build with the current toolchain"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When you have more than one toolchain installed, you can choose which one to use with the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swiftly use",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " command.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The following example illustrates installing two toolchains and explicitly using one:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly install 5.10.1",
            "$ swiftly install main-snapshot",
            "$ swiftly use 5.10.1",
            "$ swift build    # Builds with the 5.10.1 toolchain",
            "$ swift test     # Tests with the 5.10.1 toolchain",
            "$ swiftly use main-snapshot",
            "$ swift build    # Builds with the latest snapshot toolchain on the main branch",
            "$ lldb           # Run the debugger from the latest snapshot toolchain"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "use",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " command doesn’t require a full version.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "It is sufficient to provide just a major version, or the major and minor versions.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Swiftly uses the newest matching version that you have installed, if any.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly use 5",
            "swift --version  # Version matches the 5.10.1 toolchain that was installed above"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If you’re not certain which toolchain is in-use, invoke the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swiftly use",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " command to provide details:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly use",
            "Swift 5.10.1 (default)"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "You can print the exact toolchain location with the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--print-location",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flag:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly use --print-location",
            "\/Users\/someuser\/Library\/Developer\/Toolchains\/swift-5.10.1-RELEASE.xctoolchain"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Sharing-recommended-toolchain-versions",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Sharing recommended toolchain versions",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swiftly can create and update a special ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : ".swift-version",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " file at the top of your git repository so that you can share your toolchain preference with the rest of your team:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ cd path\/to\/git\/repository",
            "$ swiftly use 6.0.1",
            "A new file `path\/to\/git\/repository\/.swift-version` will be created to set the new in-use toolchain for this project.",
            "Alternatively, you can set your default globally with the `--global-default` flag. Proceed with creating this file? (Y\/n) Y",
            "$ cat .swift-version",
            "6.0.1"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When a team member uses swiftly with this git repository the toolchain that is in use matches the version in the file.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ cd path\/to\/git\/repository",
            "$ swift --version",
            "Swift version 6.0.1 (swift-6.0.1-RELEASE)",
            "Target: aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If that team member doesn’t have the toolchain installed on their system there will be an error. They can install the selected toolchain automatically like this:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ cd path\/to\/git\/repository",
            "$ swiftly install    # Installs the version of the toolchain in the .swift-version file"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If you want to temporarily use a toolchain version for one command you can try ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swiftly run",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The following command shows an example of using swiftly to build your package with the latest snapshot toolchain:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly run swift build +main-snapshot"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "The toolchain must be installed on your system before you can run with it.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swiftly uses the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : ".swift-version",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " file, if present in your working directory (or parent), to select the toolchain that is in use.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "If you are working in a directory that doesn’t have this file, then you can set a global default toolchain to use in these places.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly use --global-default 6.0.1"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Here the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--global-default",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flag ensures that the default is set globally to the “6.0.1” toolchain whenever there isn’t a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : ".swift-version",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " file, and there isn’t a version specified in the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swiftly run",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " command.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This flag doesn’t attempt to create a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : ".swift-version",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " file, or update it if it already exists.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "In-use-toolchains-and-default-toolchains",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "In use toolchains and default toolchains",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When you list installed toolchains or use the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swiftly use",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " command to print the current in use toolchain, there will be tags for both “in use” and “default.” Sometimes the same toolchain has both tags!",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly list",
            "Installed release toolchains",
            "----------------------------",
            "Swift 6.0.3",
            "Swift 6.0.2 (in use) (default)",
            "",
            "Installed snapshot toolchains",
            "-----------------------------"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Whenever a toolchain is tagged as “in use” indicates the toolchain that will be used when running toolchain commands from your current working directory.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The one that is selected is based either on what is in a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : ".swift-version",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " file or the global default if there is no such file there.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The default tag is used to show the global default toolchain, which is independent of any swift version file.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The global default is there for cases where the file doesn’t exist.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "It sets the toolchain that is in use in those cases.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
